node.accessibility_caption: Traffic waiting to cross washed out bridge in Southern Haiti

node.text:
There's a growing humanitarian crisis in Haiti. 🇭🇹 Southern Haiti is very remote. Even though the hardest hit areas are only 77 miles from Port au Prince, there is only 1 road that leads to and from. 🚗 This was the scene just  2 weeks after Hurricane Matthew hit in 2016. We sat in a long line of cars to cross a bridge that had been washed away. 🌊 The road is damaged and parts are blocked by debris that fell when the ground shook. Tropical Storm Grace caused additional mudslides that hampered efforts and the truth is-- there just aren't enough medical facilities or personnel to treat the injured. It's heartbreaking. 💔 One of the best ways to help is to donate. Today in my Stories, I'm sharing 4 organizations that are located in Southern Haiti that could use our help. I'm also giving you a way to help me how to decide how to allocate $500- $250 of my own money plus a matching gift from TextNow! Visit my Stories to learn more and vote. Haiti thanks you! 🇭🇹❤🇭🇹
#textnowpartner #haiti #ayiti #haitiearthquake #haitireliefefforts #haitiearthquake2021 #lescayes #ayiticherie

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Leticia Barr (she/her) in Haiti. May be an image of text that says 'HATT LATEST POST 4 WAYS TO HELP PROVIDE EARTHQUAKE RELIEF FOR HAITI'.

node.text:
Haiti is always in my heart and on my mind but especially over the past few days. 💔 
I appreciate every single person who has reached out to ask about how to help provide earthquake relief for Haiti. 🇭🇹
Today my post is live (link in bio!). It shares personal experiences from numerous trips to the country (8-9 in 5 years) and working with artisans, including those in Les Cayes and Camp-Perrin, communities in Southern Haiti that were hardest hit by the earthquake. 💔
You can read why strong earthquakes keep happen in Haiti, why it's good to be skeptical about who to donate to when disaster strikes, and 4 ways to help, including 8 trusted organizations I know are doing great work on the ground right now. I truly appreciate you trusting me to share ways you can help and ensure donations go to the right organizations. As you can imagine, I feel a huge responsibility to the country that I love dearly and the people I've met over the years who I hold close in my heart.🇭🇹❤🇭🇹
#haiti #haitiearthquake #southernhaiti #lescayes #ayiti #ayiticherie

node.text:
Sunday reads. 📰 So many things are on my mind today as I read today's headlines. Aftershocks rock Haiti as Tropical Storm Grace heads towards the part of the island that suffered the most earthquake damage and the Taliban's continued advances in Afghanistan means women and girls are at risk of a humanitarian crisis. 😥 Now that I've consumed some news, it's time for me to stop because that's what's healthy for me right now. 🙏 Instead I'm going to focus on finding and sharing good ways to help in Haiti through my Instagram Stories. 🇭🇹Also-- issue 1 of year 2 of @stanchionzine that arrived in my mailbox yesterday! The 60 pages of stories, poems, monologues, and photos bound and printed on heavy paper is just what I need right now! 💕 Take care of yourselves, friends. You matter. And if you don't know about Stanchion, check it out! It's by my good friend, @owtk and I'm proud to say I've been a subscriber since the beginning! 📚
#sunday #amreading #news #stanchionzine #literaryzine #haiti #haitiearthquake #washingtonpost

node.accessibility_caption: Haiti earthquake breaking news

node.text:
Heartbreaking news out of Haiti. 🇭🇹 There's been a 7.2 earthquake in Haiti with the epicenter located in the southern part and felt as far away as the Bahamas. For perspective, this quake is more powerful than the 7.0 quake in 2010. 🌎 The magnitude scale is logarithmic. According to @sciencemagazine, this means that "if you add 1 to an earthquake's magnitude, you multiply the shaking by 10. Fractional differences work the same way. Increase the magnitude by 0.1, and you multiply the shaking by 10^(0.1), or about 1.259—an increase of 26%. Increase the magnitude by 0.3, and the shaking almost exactly doubles." 🤯 I have heard from my dear friend, @explore_with_nat, that things are not good, especially for artisans in the South & Grandanse (Les Cayes, Aquin, Jérémie). I personally know people who have lost everything. Their homes are completely destroyed. There are fears of a tsunami in Les Cayes, a city on the southern tip I visited 2 weeks after Hurricane Matthew destroyed the area to bring your donated relief supplies. 💔 Haiti will need our help but if you're going to donate to any relief group- please wait! After the 2010 quake we saw so many relief organizations pop up that had minimal impact and I would be happy to share more information when I get it from my trusted sources who I've been working with on philanthropic ventures in Haiti for years. 🇭🇹❤🇭🇹
#haiti #haitiearthquake #ayiti #ayiticherie

node.text:
Flashback Friday to my first day as a middle school teacher! {ad} I won't lie- I'm excited to return to in-person learning but this year comes with a mix of emotions. 🙂🤪🥰😳😂🙄😎
Our kids may seem happy and well adjusted but living and learning during the pandemic has been stressful. 🤯 Today on the blog I'm sharing ways you prepare your kids for returning to school by supporting their social emotional learning at home. 🏡 Working together to plan ahead, get organized, and help kids feel safe makes them feel supported and ready for what the school year brings. 👩‍🏫
Even if school has started in your area, it's never too late to start the important social and emotional work can help ease school anxiety. 🚸 I know there are questions about going back to school so I'm partnering with @textnow on an Ask Me Anything series.❓ Leave a comment below asking me any anything related to the school year. If you need the weekend to think, you can also ask on Monday through the Instagram Stories questions feature. I'll be sharing questions parents have and my answers in my Stories next week! 🎉 Have a great Friday and ask me anything as you head back to school!😘
#textnowpartner #backtoschool #teacher #middleschoolteacher #STEMteacher #teacherlife #teachersofIG #teachinginapandemic #wecandoit #flashbackfriday
